---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service | FindVolleyball" description="The terms for using FindVolleyball and submitting listings.">
  <main class="terms-page">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <p>
      FindVolleyball is a small, free, community-run project — these terms are written in plain language for the
      same reason. By using the site, you agree to them. If anything here is unclear, email
      <a href="mailto:robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com">robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com</a> and ask.
    </p>

    <h2>What FindVolleyball is</h2>
    <p>
      A free, community-driven map of volleyball meetups. Anyone can browse it without an account. Submitting a
      listing, voting, or reporting requires a free account for some actions and not others, as noted where you
      encounter them.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content</h2>
    <p>
      If you submit a listing — including its name, schedule, photo, notes, or any link — you're responsible for
      it being accurate and for having the right to share it (e.g. a photo you actually took or have permission
      to use). Don't submit anything illegal, harassing, deliberately false, or that infringes someone else's
      rights.
    </p>
    <p>
      Submissions are reviewed before they appear on the public map, but that review is a basic accuracy/sanity
      check, not a guarantee. We can edit, reject, or remove any listing at any time, for any reason, including
      content that violates these terms or just looks wrong.
    </p>

    <h2>No guarantee of accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      Listing details — whether a meetup is still happening, its schedule, cost, or anything else — are supplied
      by the community and can be outdated or wrong. <strong>Always verify directly with the organizer or venue
      before showing up</strong>, especially for anything marked "Decayed." Use the map at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party links</h2>
    <p>
      Listings often link out to external signup pages, Meetup groups, or contact info. We don't control those
      sites and aren't responsible for what's on them.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      The site is provided "as is," with no warranty of any kind. We don't guarantee it'll be available,
      error-free, or uninterrupted. To the extent allowed by law, we're not liable for any damages — including
      anything that happens at a meetup you found through this site — arising from your use of it.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      These terms may change as the project evolves. Continuing to use the site after a change means you accept
      the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com">robert.tyler.miller@gmail.com</a> with any questions
      about these terms.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .terms-page {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 32rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;

    h1 {
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .updated {
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: #888;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 1.75rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      font-weight: 600;
    }
  }
</style>
